text.section:
The General Assembly finds that:
many residents of the State hold policies issued by insurers and other persons not authorized to do insurance business in the State;
these residents face the often insurmountable obstacle of asserting their legal rights under those policies in forums that are foreign to them and under laws and rules of practice that are unfamiliar to them; and
protection from the acts of insurers and other persons not authorized to do insurance business in the State can be achieved by:
maintaining fair and honest insurance markets;
protecting the premium tax revenues of the State;
protecting authorized insurers, which are subject to strict regulation, from unfair competition by unauthorized persons and unauthorized insurers; and
protecting against evasion of the insurance regulatory laws of the State.
